defaultRetaining the supply of women in STEM is inseparably linked to ensuring supply is fluid, fertile and unimpeded. Strategies for retaining women in STEM must therefor
defaulte focus not only in responding to the needs of those in STEM employment or even those enrolled in STEM university courses, but have a life-course vision which begins with the early initiation of prospective female scientists.
