default&#xa0;default&#xa0;default&#xa0;default4. defaultBuilding critical massdefault4.1 
defaultThe gendered construction of S
defaultTEM may only fully destabilize, where sufficient numbers of women combine to contest and defeat prejudice and processes which delimit and/or deny their participation, ascent and acceleration in STEM careers.   
default&#xa0;
default4.2 
defaultThe persistence of unequal gendered repr
defaultesentation in STEM, results not only from a lack of consistency in terms of occupational conditions and opportunities by gender, but by the very fact that a lack of female representation in STEM diminishes the audibility and authority of the counter-claim.
default In other words, a culture of resistance that might disrupt discriminatory practice in STEM
default 
defaultdepends on the mobilization of a collective and unified voice of objection. In this context, we believe it 
defaulterroneous 
defaultto isolate and/or quarantine young female learn
defaulters of STEM from the realities of their potential/chosen profession. Female learners should instead be made explicitly aware of issues of unequal and discriminatory gender practice in STEM, yet concurrently, be provided with the necessary tools with which 
defaultto combat and hopefully, overturn all forms of prejudice and inequity. 
default&#xa0;
default4.3 
defaultIt is, in our opinion, albeit well-intentioned, a misplaced strategy to insulate, protect and conceal from female learners and aspirant women scientists the harsh realities of 
defaulttheir occupational futures. A more pragmatic approach is in providing female learners
default and early career scientists
default with th
defaulte right kinds of emotional and intellectual scaffolding
default 
defaultthat will allow them to pre-empt, circumvent or counter the inevitability of ex
defaultposure to forms of work-based gender discrimination. The female collective in science is an essential part of early career support; a key weapon in the armoury against gender discrimination; and the platform from which to fight for and further the rights o
defaultf women in STEM. Quintessentially, the 
defaultretainment
default of women in STEM demands increased recruitment in STEM where a critical mass and the power 
defaultof many enables
default and enforces
default change. 
