defaultperhaps even more deleterious to
default the science community. Crucially, science is not for everyone. N
defaultot every girl
default, nor for that matter
default every boy
default,
default will be well suited to science career. For that matter STEM is not ‘the be all and end all’. Whilst STEM is massively important and provides an indispensable skill set for all learners, we should not presume th
defaultat every child will have interest in science or necessarily want to be a scientist. This is the more tacit danger when pursuing a STEM agenda, not least one among girls. We should not lose sight of the multiple other kinds of occupations outside of STEM 
defaultno
defaultr become so infatuated with its promotion, that we find ourselves recruiting into STEM the kinds 
defaultof individuals whose talents and
